And no, I don't remember off the top of my head what experiments can/have been done...I'm not a physicist, I just happen to take an interest in it.<br>
<br>
I should mention that the effects you're looking for, like a pencil not dropping to the ground, are on the macroscopic level.  The chances of the billions of particles cooperating in such a way are--while nonzero--extremely small, which is why we have not observed it.  However, if you look on a much smaller scale, the probabilities of similar events increase to the point where we can observe them (if indirectly) on occasion.<br>
<br>
